   <h1>Why is it Beneficial?</h1>

<p>As a high school student, the world may seem like a large and intimidating place. Outbound is a perfect way to view the world in a new light, to gain a new life changing experience, and to increase your knowledge of an ever-changing world. Many students ask, &quot;Why should I study abroad?&quot; The answers are many, but here are a few great reasons to study abroad:</p>
<ul><li>Learn a new culture and gain a perspective on your own life in the United States that you can only obtain by living and studying in another country.
<li>You can stand out and be unique on a college application. As college admissions become more and more competitive, nothing is more unique and makes you shine brighter than studying abroad in another country for a semester or a year.
<li>Learning a new language is a valuable skill-set to have that can set you apart from others as you move forward in college and beyond.</li></ul>








